Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.43,0:00:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, to the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.97,0:00:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.77,0:00:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the hospital so they can treat you and you can get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.98,0:00:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You promised to tell me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.77,0:00:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer to your deduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.30,0:00:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.94,0:00:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because maybe I have a feeling that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.03,0:00:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree with your reasoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.20,0:00:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.91,0:00:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, until you go to the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.29,0:00:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not letting go of your hand, never!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.57,0:00:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.30,0:00:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A desperate crisis...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.04,0:00:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A splendid revival reverses the conclusion to a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.31,0:00:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The terms of the engagement are "No Smoking!"...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.97,0:00:47.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And yet, for reasons unknown, there's a huge explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.32,0:00:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.92,0:00:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.77,0:00:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.29,0:02:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.71,0:02:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wake up, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.26,0:02:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.97,0:02:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your cold all right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others headed to the airport in\NMouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s car so they could get back to Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.81,0:02:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.27,0:03:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.52,0:03:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you let go of my hand sometime soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.28,0:03:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry. Did it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.36,0:03:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.49,0:03:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's funny...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I was holding onto Shinichi's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I suddenly felt faint...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because I shot you with the spare tranquilizer gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.67,0:03:25.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's because you were really tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.63,0:03:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You kept holding onto his hand the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.51,0:03:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when Shinichi was carrying you and putting you in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Shinichi? Did he go in my dad's car also?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.72,0:03:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he rested in my car for a bit until he was feeling better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.36,0:03:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He left saying he had some unfinished case to tidy up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.98,0:03:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he shook himself free of my hand and left?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.24,0:03:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mystery-loving prince of fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.45,0:03:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prince of fools?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.91,0:03:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's too bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was so determined not to let go of his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.92,0:04:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at the left side of Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.38,0:04:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See how it's been cut from the cuff all the way\Nto the hem and sealed with safety pins?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.26,0:04:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves he put on the sweater while\Nyou were still holding his left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.81,0:04:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, you really have nothing to regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.73,0:04:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no. Is your cold coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.44,0:04:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine. I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.49,0:04:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was thanks to that little girl putting the girl from\Nthe detective agency to sleep with the tranquilizer gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you weren't found out in the end, even though\Nyou shrank in the car while still holding hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.88,0:04:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holding hands? Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old man, Agasa, told me over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.93,0:04:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor... Keep your mouth shut...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.22,0:05:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you did get some of it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.31,0:05:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The drug that changes you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.27,0:05:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be better if you had that drug with\Nyou, just in case it becomes necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.19,0:05:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what I thought, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.65,0:05:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, didn't I just tell you guys not to eavesdrop?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudou...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.53,0:05:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. Ignore that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.49,0:05:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're all on the way to go camping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.50,0:05:26.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.59,0:05:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked Haibara to give me a hundred tablets of that drug to start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.01,0:05:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hundred?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.47,0:05:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:38.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think even that much will be enough though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.89,0:05:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm warning you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.85,0:05:44.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each time you take the drug, your body builds up more resistance to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.98,0:05:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it grows less effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.11,0:05:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I truly don't know if you'll be able to return to your former body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since you want to act cool for that girl at the detective agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:06:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might not even last a week, even with a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.58,0:06:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like she needed to tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.62,0:06:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, Kudou...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.37,0:06:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the little girl tells you not to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.04,0:06:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better if you tell the girl at\Nthe detective agency the whole story?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.30,0:06:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way you can confess your love sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.80,0:06:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.59,0:06:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.35,0:06:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I can't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.26,0:06:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What can't you do (ika-nai)?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.89,0:06:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't go (ika-nee) camping with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no... it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.27,0:06:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! We're going camping in the mountains.\NThere's no way there'll be a squid (ika) there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you're talking about on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, I've already finished talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey! Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.83,0:06:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.42,0:06:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.05,0:06:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is going to be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.84,0:06:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The campground we're going to, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.72,0:06:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.67,0:06:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it has really beautiful scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.89,0:07:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what should we have for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought lots of ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I want a barbecue!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You always want that, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.31,0:07:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you like, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The usual - curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.40,0:07:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.82,0:07:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter. If I were in the mood to eat, anything would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, don't pay attention to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.91,0:07:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she's been like this since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet she's worrying about something silly again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.64,0:07:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the engine died again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you have it checked before we left?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.93,0:07:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and thanks to that, the engine's running perfectly...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.40,0:07:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, as for the gasoline, we're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.98,0:07:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, it's getting dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.40,0:08:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd better hurry and call someone to bring us some gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.70,0:08:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:05.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so too. That's why I'm calling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.45,0:08:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.58,0:08:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, the person who's been living next door to\Nme since that incident with the fire - Okiya Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he said he'd be relaxing at home all day today...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.71,0:08:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't mind spending two hours coming out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? We're out of the cellphone service range here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:25.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'll we do!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.81,0:08:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here in the middle of the mountains!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.68,0:08:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're still pretty far from the campground, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.10,0:08:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For now, we have three choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.69,0:08:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Walk back to the gasoline stand we passed by\Naround thirty minutes ago, and buy some gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.20,0:08:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay here and wait until a car happens by, and\Nthen ask them to take us to the gasoline stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.54,0:08:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We go to that villa viewable on the mountain\Nabove and ask to borrow their phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it'd take us more than two hours\Nto get back to the gas stand on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.05,0:09:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we haven't seen many cars pass by\Non this mountain road, it'd be tough to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.18,0:09:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I think the safest bet is to\Nhead to that villa while it's still light out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.02,0:09:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.63,0:09:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a princess lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.86,0:09:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they'll serve us food when we get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may get a full course of French cooking!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.28,0:09:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want Italian!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.49,0:09:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you came to go camping.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.29,0:09:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, stop, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.84,0:09:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry, but could you take us to a nearby gasoline stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.33,0:09:54.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.85,0:09:56.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Could you give me a few more details?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.97,0:09:56.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Sudou Gouki (34)\N{\fs12} IT Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, we were on our way to a campground...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.57,0:10:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And happened to run out of gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.11,0:10:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we're out of cellphone range, we're in a quandary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.66,0:10:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.00,0:10:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here until you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.16,0:10:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You old goat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.80,0:10:26.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.47,0:10:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an unpleasant person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.64,0:10:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we may well have to beg for help\Nfrom that unpleasant fellow once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.14,0:10:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.90,0:10:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That car was one that has ridiculously high maintenance costs...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.86,0:10:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A classic car that rich people prefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.53,0:10:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person driving a car like that around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.28,0:10:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might just be the same rich person who built\Nthis luxury villa in the middle of these mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.79,0:10:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's not ask him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.91,0:10:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:11:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd rather wait here until another car\Ncomes than ask someone like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.67,0:11:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there's a chance that guy wasn't going to\Nthe villa, but to a completely different place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.51,0:11:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be a bad idea to go and check, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.39,0:11:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.97,0:11:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's leave the luggage in the car and go together to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.48,0:11:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if we all ask together...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.98,0:11:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, we should at least take a flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.19,0:11:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is getting dark, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.28,0:11:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in the pocket beneath the driver's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you get it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.49,0:11:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with you? You're acting like a queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.83,0:11:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that what it looks like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.63,0:11:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's gotten into you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.54,0:11:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we're camping...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.01,0:11:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.43,0:11:56.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.89,0:11:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The emblem from that guy's car!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.73,0:12:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.69,0:12:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was the same car as before...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.69,0:12:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did it explode?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.61,0:12:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the bomb planted on it from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.28,0:12:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was the reason he didn't give us a ride because\Nhe didn't want us to be caught in the explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be. It didn't seem that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.96,0:12:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, Ena! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.13,0:12:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.97,0:12:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called for a fire truck and an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.97,0:12:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, did that Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.98,0:12:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he have dyed brown hair, a beard, and wear\Na black fleece jacket over a wool sweatshirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.69,0:12:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who... are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man like that, driving a classic car, passed us on the road a bit ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.29,0:13:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased was Sudou Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 34.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he was a company president who made a ton of money\Nfrom his IT business, which let him build this gorgeous villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.34,0:13:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of the fire was a cigarette he was smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.10,0:13:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cigarette he was smoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.47,0:13:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a plastic container in the garage with\Ngasoline inside had accidentally tipped over...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.94,0:13:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which ended up filling the garage with gasoline fumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.23,0:13:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived in his car\Nand opened the door of the garage...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.03,0:13:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was smoking inside the stopped car, and in\Nthe moment he stepped out, the fire erupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire completely engulfed the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found a burnt cigarette butt, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.28,0:13:49.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he had quit smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.83,0:13:49.84,CharCard2,,0,0,0,,Ginbayashi Ena (31)\N{\fs13} Sudou's Fiancee
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.34,0:13:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate cigarettes, so he did it for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.80,0:13:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm - who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:13:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's Sudou's fiancee, Ginbayashi Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the weekends, everyone usually gets together here for parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tonight, Sudou was supposed to announce something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.61,0:14:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd finally decided on the day for our wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was planning to announce it to everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.91,0:14:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then... and then... why did this have to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.99,0:14:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, since we found a burnt marriage license...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.58,0:14:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you're saying appears to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as for giving up smoking, it looks like that was a lie, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ashtray in that car had a large number of cigarette butts in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next to the body, in addition to the burnt cigarette...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.93,0:14:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd dropped a bag that contained a\Nsealed carton of cigarettes and a lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.69,0:14:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was just telling him to stop smoking a little while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.48,0:14:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little while ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got a phone call from Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about\Nan hour ago that said he was on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.87,0:15:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During that call, Ena told him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.41,0:15:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you don't quit smoking, then our engagement is off!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that phone call really from Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who answered the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.09,0:15:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I talked with him before hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.42,0:15:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So not only did Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} not quit smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.01,0:15:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He ignored the recommended way to store\Ngasoline, and used a plastic container.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.05,0:15:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} suffered the consequences...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.43,0:15:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.81,0:15:28.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't say that for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.02,0:15:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, if Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got out of the\Ncar with a cigarette in his mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.40,0:15:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he took the cigarette out and\Nlit it shortly before he got out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.61,0:15:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet it isn't here anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.41,0:15:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The open cigarette pack, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.66,0:15:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mr. Forensics guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.75,0:15:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-ls that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.33,0:15:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we couldn't find it in the car, the garage, or anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.34,0:15:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why isn't it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.38,0:16:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cigarette butt might have been thrown in the\Ngarage before Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived, might it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.43,0:16:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.06,0:16:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean this wasn't just an accident, but\Nwas probably planned by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.06,0:16:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may have been murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.61,0:16:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.53,0:16:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the polyethylene tank placed in the garage had tipped over...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gasoline vaporized and filled the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whereupon Sudou Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought his car inside the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.00,0:16:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stopped the car and the instance he got out\Nwith a cigarette in his mouth, it exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.84,0:16:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They even found the cigarette butt\Nthat caused the fire inside the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.39,0:16:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first glance, it appears to just be an accident, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they can't find the open cigarette pack the victim\Nsupposedly took the cigarette from anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:17:03.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means the cigarette butt had already\Nbeen in the garage before Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.37,0:17:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it may be a fake piece of evidence that the culprit\Nleft in order to make it look like an accidental death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.75,0:17:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.46,0:17:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.21,0:17:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've been investigating the garage for some time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't found anything that looked like a detonator.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.39,0:17:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't have a cigarette case or anything either, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.72,0:17:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's definitely strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.77,0:17:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet if you search more, you'll find something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.40,0:17:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.73,0:17:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cigarette was the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.86,0:17:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So couldn't he have thrown the empty pack out\Nthe car window before he went into the garage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.53,0:17:53.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always used to crumple empty\Ncigarette packs into a ball and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.33,0:18:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, are you saying that if we search around\Nthe villa, we'll find that empty pack?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.67,0:18:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.88,0:18:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but he may have thrown the empty pack out a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.39,0:18:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had lied about quitting smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think he'd avoid throwing it out around the villa?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.81,0:18:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, it would expand the field of\Nsearch greatly, making it difficult to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.02,0:18:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the deep valley along the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.61,0:18:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's all I can think of...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.82,0:18:26.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.45,0:18:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you really believe that Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had quit smoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:35.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had found out that he was secretly smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.79,0:18:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would have only had to drop the plastic\Ngasoline tanks inside the garage and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.38,0:18:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.63,0:18:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody's noticed Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} secretly smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.59,0:18:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.63,0:18:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never smoked a single cigarette since said he was quitting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.26,0:18:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was just in front of you guys, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We met Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} a little while ago, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a brazen liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.77,0:19:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought his fiancee might know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.11,0:19:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brazen liar?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.86,0:19:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.78,0:19:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had run out of gas on our way to a campground...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.03,0:19:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we stopped Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who happened\Nto be passing by on the same road.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.79,0:19:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked him to take us to the gasoline stand, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.75,0:19:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he was real mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.54,0:19:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we went over by the driver's seat and explained the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.67,0:19:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first that guy said "Get on in," but then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He swore at us and drove away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.80,0:19:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here until you die, you old goat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.10,0:19:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, that's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to speak ill of the dead, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.73,0:19:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't seem like the kind of person who\Nwould keep a promise to quit smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.02,0:19:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That does sound like something he would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought he'd keep his promise to quit smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was madly in love with Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.57,0:19:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's assume - and this is just an assumption...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.99,0:20:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I knew that Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was secretly smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.71,0:20:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way here, he called me on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.25,0:20:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I said in front of everyone that if he didn't\Nstop smoking our engagement was off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.38,0:20:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could predict that he'd go against that\Nand get out of the car with a cigarette in his mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.97,0:20:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after I told him not to smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.81,0:20:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just as she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.31,0:20:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing that she told him not to smoke in front of everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.15,0:20:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be hard to prove that she's the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.48,0:20:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the cigarette didn't start the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether he stopped smoking or not, I can't tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.41,0:20:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, for today at least, I don't think he was smoking inside his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.12,0:20:41.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the Professor stopped him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.62,0:20:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went up to the driver's side too, and there was no smell of cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.46,0:20:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how did the fire in the garage start?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.51,0:20:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm still not sure about that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.63,0:20:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am sure that Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the one who set it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.98,0:21:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try to remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.06,0:21:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the start, when Inspector Yuminaga said the cause of the\Nfire was his smoking, Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} flared up at him while crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.32,0:21:12.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he had quit smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.20,0:21:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, only a little while after those\Nwords came out of her mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.66,0:21:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a response to me pointing out how it was strange\Nthat there were no opened cigarette packs around...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.66,0:21:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't he have thrown it out the car\Nwindow before he went into the garage?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.79,0:21:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had really believed that he'd quit smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't she normally have agreed with what I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.88,0:21:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It's just like I thought. He did quit smoking."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.64,0:21:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.10,0:21:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.60,0:21:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her inconsistent words all add up if they're from the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.73,0:21:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her flare up at Inspector Yuminaga was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.90,0:21:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I didn't know he was secretly smoking!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.78,0:21:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While her objection to me was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.49,0:21:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The cause of the fire was most definitely the lit cigarette."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.62,0:22:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.37,0:22:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wants, at all costs, for this to look like\Nan accidental death due to smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.00,0:22:08.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it wasn't an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.79,0:22:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire was set up on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.30,0:22:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, don't they say, "There can't be smoke without fire"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.26,0:22:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm thinking about right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.47,0:22:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's got to be something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.93,0:22:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some trick to starting that fire in the garage without using a detonator.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.68,0:24:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.47,0:24:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wool Sweater
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.84,0:24:25.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.84,0:24:21.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, there's a fuzzball on your sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.26,0:24:22.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's because it's wool.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.17,0:24:23.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, there's a price tag on your sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.54,0:24:24.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's because it's on sale.
